          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-20 13:42:52" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to refuse to listen to and hence to disobey</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to refuse to listen</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to refuse to obey</Gloss>
                <Gloss>disobedience</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It would be a mistake to translate παρακούω[a], παρακοή, and παραιτέομαι[e] as meaning nothing more than ‘not to listen to.’ The meaning is clearly ‘to refuse to listen to’ or ‘to refuse to pay attention to,’ and hence ‘to disobey.’ It may therefore be best in a number of instances to translate ‘to refuse to obey.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
